      "writtenOn": "2020-10-20T01:56:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, crap. The feature I was hoping to use to avoid prpc code generation was reverted in https://github.com/grpc/grpc-go/commit/02cd07d9bb5609fe76f8bb8d948037e79a8b29c7 :-/ \n\nBefore that CL, generated _grpc.pb.go had:\n\n  func RegisterServiceName(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, impl ...)\n\nWhere https://godoc.org/google.golang.org/grpc#ServiceRegistrar is actually already implemented by *prpc.Server.\n\nNow generated code has (just like it did initially):\n\n  func RegisterServiceName(s *grpc.Server, ...)\n\n:(\n\nSo I guess I\u0027ll just 🙈 and keep using old grpc plugin and custom code generator. This CL is still useful since it updates to newer protobuf library.",
